ENTRY            F0721   20251230   20260311   20260311       F107
SUBENT        F0721001   20251230   20260311   20260311       F107
BIB                 14         37
TITLE      Parities of states in 15O and 33Cl
AUTHOR     (S.Mubarakmand,B.E.F.Macefield)
INSTITUTE  (2UK OXF)
REFERENCE  (J,NP/A,98,82,1967)
FACILITY   (VDGT,2UK OXF)
INC-SOURCE 5.08 MeV deuteron beam.
INC-SPECT  Main set of deflector plates sweeps the beam in a
           horizontal plane at 10 MHz and another set sweeps it
           in a vertical plane at 5 MHz. Beam bursts of duration
           less than one nsec. The average current is about 20 nA.
DETECTOR   (SCIN) NE213 liquid scintillator, 2.5 cm thick and
           25 cm in diameter, was used for neutron detection. This
           is coupled with two XP1040 photomultiplier tubes.
           A second time-of-flight spectrometer using a 12.5 cm
           diameter scintillator is used to provide the monitoring
           for the experiments.
METHOD     (TOF)
SAMPLE     Gas targets were used. The main section of target
           assembly was made from stainless steel tubing 2.25 cm
           in diameter. Into this tube slip in two 1.9 cm diameter
           tubes through O ring seals. One end of a "slip-in" tube
           was open while an aperture was mounted on the other
           end. A nickel foil was soldered on this aperture. The
           stopping power of the nickel foil was about 80 keV.
MONITOR    (1-H-2(D,N)2-HE-3,,DA) Detector efficiency was
           determined by studying this reaction. Deuterium gas
           target 0.36 mg/cm2 thick was used and relative
           efficiency curve was plotted covering a range of
           neutron energies from 1.8 to 11.3 MeV.
           Second time-of-flight spectrometer using a 12.5 cm
           diameter was used to provide the monitoring for the
           experiments.
MONIT-REF  (,J.E.Brolley+,B,FAST N.PH.,,,1973)
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information on source of uncertainties
HISTORY    (20050627C)
           (20160424U) SD: Small correction in MONIT-REF.
           (20251230U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              37
COMMON               1          3
EN
MEV
 5.0
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           44
